products.name: Jack Daniel's Legacy 1905 Edition Limit One
products.description: Jack Daniel's Tennesse Whiskey is the world's best selling whiskey. Every bottle of smooth Tennessee Whiskey is distilled and bottled at the Jack Daniel Whiskey Distillery in Lynchburg, Tennessee. Established in 1866, the Jack Daniel Whiskey Distillery is the oldest registered distillery in America. This American Whiskey is made from the finest corn, rye, and barley malt. These choice grains are mixed with the iron-free water that flows from the Cave Spring right on grounds of the whiskey distillery. From there Jack Daniel's Tennessee Whiskey is charcoal mellowed, drop by drop, through 10 feet of sugar maple charcoal, which imparts the distinct sweet smoothness of this best in class whiskey. Finally, Jack Daniel's Tennesse Whiskey is matured in handcrafted white oak barrels of our own making. Whether you want your whiskey neat, whiskey on the rocks, or in your favorite cocktail like an Old Fashioned, Jack Daniel's whiskey is there.

products.name: Jack Daniel's Legacy Edition Series Second Edition
products.description:
Just like the name ‘Old No. 7,’ the history of our label is a bit of a mystery. Some say we chose the color to mourn Mr. Jack’s death; others don't think we chose it for any reason at all. We may never know for sure, but we are certain this label was one of the very first times it was predominantly black. 

 

Our second bottling in the Jack Daniel's Legacy Edition Series is a return to one of the first instances of Jack's iconic black label. It's a symbol of our enduring spirit, an ode to Mr. Jack's color of choice and, well, just a good bottle of whiskey. So enjoy a sip or two of Jack Daniel's history.

products.name: Jack Daniel's Single Barrel Tennessee Rye Whiskey
products.description: In Lynchburg, we discover a new Tennessee whiskey every day. That’s because every day we sample our barrels and find one that is unique enough for our Single Barrel collection. One may be sweeter. One might have more oak. But each is hand-selected for its own, singular take on our Tennessee Whiskey. Jack Daniel’s Single Barrel Rye is bold and balanced, carefully mellowed to be sippin' smooth, yet spicy and complex. Each barrel is hand selected from the highest reaches of the barrel house and bottled in the smallest of batches, just one barrel at a time, at 94 proof with robust character and notes of caramel and baking spice.

products.name: Jack Daniel's Tennessee Straight Rye Whiskey
products.description: Jack Daniel's Tennessee Rye Whiskey combines the distinct flavor of rye with the one-of-a-kind taste of classic Jack Daniel's Whiskey. This American whiskey is made with a uniquely crafted 70-percent rye grain bill, natural spring water from Jack Daniel's own Cave Spring Hollow, and a time-honored charcoal mellowing process that results in a bold, spicy Rye Whiskey that's sippin' smooth. At 90 proof, it packs rich flavors from start to finish. Jack Daniel's Tennessee Rye Whiskey brings out a sweet caramel taste, followed by a peppery finish. Jack Daniel's Rye Whiskey alcohol can be enjoyed neat, on the rocks, or in your favorite mixed drinks like a Rye Old Fashioned, a Manhattan cocktail or a Jack Rye & Ginger. Please Drink Responsibly.

products.name: Jack Daniel's Tennessee Whiskey
products.description: Jack Daniel's Single Barrel rewards our friend, Eric Church. This limited-edition Jack Daniel's was hand-selected to celebrate the long-standing friendship between Jack Daniel's and Eric Church.  Each barrel is unique from the highest reaches of the barre house that our master distiller, Jeff Arnett, selected to Eric's taste profile.  This one-of-kind offering is bottled at 94 proof with a muted sweet notes of vanilla and caramel upon entry, full-bodied and creamy at mid-palate, warm, and lingering toasted oak on the finish.

products.name: Jack Daniel's Triple Mash Blended Straight Whiskey 100proof
products.description:
Jack Daniel’s Triple Mash is a blend of three straight Bottled In- Bond whiskeys: 60% Jack Daniel’s Tennessee Rye, 20% Jack Daniel’s Tennessee Whiskey and 20% Jack Daniel’s American Malt. Each expression is distilled in Lynchburg, TN, in the same distilling season, aged to the stipulations of the Bottled in Bond Act, then blended and bottled at 100 proof.

Jack Daniel’s Triple Mash has notes of honey, malt and soft oak, the company reports.

products.name: Jack Daniel's Whiskey Single Barrel Select Proof Rye
products.description: In Lynchburg, we discover a new whiskey every day. That’s because every day we sample our barrels and find ones that are unique enough for our Single Barrel collection. One may be sweeter. One might have more oak. But each is hand-selected for its own, singular take on our Tennessee Whiskey. Jack Daniel's Single Barrel Barrel Proof is whiskey as nature intended it—bottled straight from the barrel at its full proof. Intense, smooth, and remarkably varied, Barrel Proof is bottled at anywhere from 125 to 140-proof, taking Jack’s trademark vanilla and toasted oak flavors to bold new levels.
